CSC249 has the course title "Machine Vision". CSC249 is a 4.0 credit course taught by Chenliang Xu. CSC249 is offered every Fall. Introduction to computer vision, including camera models, basic image processing, pattern and object recognition, and elements of human vision. Specific topics include geometric issues, statistical models, Hough transforms, color theory, texture, and optic flow. CSC449, a graduate-level course, requires additional readings and assignments.Prerequisites: MTH161 and CSC242; MTH165 strongly recommended